{"_id":"Spicytomatopastasauce","preptime":"15","servings":"4","keywords":["diet@vegetarian","cook method.hob, oven, grill@hob","diet@corn-free","cuisine@european.italian","meal type@misc","meal type@main","diet@egg-free","diet@cow dairy-free","diet@wheat-free","diet@peanut-free","diet@dairy-free","special collections@very easy","diet@citrus-free","diet@shellfish-free","diet@vegan","main ingredient@pasta","diet@demi-veg","diet@gluten-free"],"subtitle":"You could use fresh or canned tomatoes, or passata for this recipe.","totaltime":"22","cooktime":"7","ingredients":[{"ingredient":"olive oil","measure":"3 tsp"},{"ingredient":"red onion","measure":"1"},{"ingredient":"garlic","measure":"1 clove"},{"ingredient":"canned chopped tomatoes","measure":"1 kg"},{"ingredient":"chillies","measure":"2"},{"ingredient":"fresh oregano","measure":"2 sprigs"},{"ingredient":"salt","measure":"[sup]1[/sup]/[sub]2[/sub] tsp"},{"ingredient":"sugar","measure":"[sup]1[/sup]/[sub]4[/sub] tsp"},{"ingredient":"black pepper","measure":"[sup]1[/sup]/[sub]4[/sub] tsp"},{"ingredient":"red wine vinegar","measure":"1 tsp"}],"method":[{"step":"1","text":"Heat oil in a large pan. Fry onion and garlic for 5 min. Add tomatoes and chillies (or hot pepper sauce). Slowly bring to boil. Cover and simmer for 8 min."},{"step":"2","text":"Strip the leaves from the oregano stems and chop the leaves. Add to the tomato sauce with salt, sugar, pepper and vinegar. Simmer for 2 min. "},{"step":"3","text":"Serve with cooked pasta. "}],"title":"Spicy tomato pasta sauce"}